1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,560
HealthPulse AI, 11 MCP tools, one healthcare platform.

2
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:05,840
First question to the agent,

3
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:08,920
show me quality anomalies in California hospitals.

4
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:11,120
Behind this chat, HealthPulse isn't an app,

5
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:13,120
it's a Model Context Protocol server.

6
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:16,200
11 healthcare intelligence tools that any MCP client,

7
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:19,240
Claude Desktop, Prompt Opinion, the Anthropic API,

8
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:21,000
a custom agent, can invoke by name.

9
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,160
Right now, Claude is calling the quality monitor tool

10
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:26,639
against 233,000 rows of real CMS data,

11
00:00:26,639 --> 00:00:30,360
computing Z-scores across all 5,400 U.S. hospitals.

12
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:33,880
No dashboards, no thresholds, structured output,

13
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:35,840
a host model can reason over.

14
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:38,959
And here's the finding, UCI Health Los Alamitos,

15
00:00:38,959 --> 00:00:42,360
48% higher hip and knee readmissions than expected.

16
00:00:42,360 --> 00:00:45,279
Oroville and Kaweah Health flagged as repeat offenders,

17
00:00:45,279 --> 00:00:47,119
not threshold alerts.

18
00:00:47,119 --> 00:00:49,680
Statistical pattern detection across an entire state

19
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,480
in a single tool call.

20
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:54,639
Next query, what's the equity disparity in Texas?

21
00:00:54,639 --> 00:00:56,480
The equity detector tool is now correlating

22
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,160
every Texas hospital star rating

23
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:00,799
against the CDC Social Vulnerability Index,

24
00:01:00,799 --> 00:01:02,040
county by county.

25
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:04,440
Same primitive, different tool.

26
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:07,000
A Dallas County paradox, vulnerable communities

27
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,440
receiving two-star care while UT Southwestern

28
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,160
next door runs four-star.

29
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:13,320
Systemic disparity, one tool call.

30
00:01:13,320 --> 00:01:15,519
The executive briefing tool aggregates state data

31
00:01:15,519 --> 00:01:17,639
into a board-ready analysis.

32
00:01:17,639 --> 00:01:21,959
California, 378 facilities, 3.01 average stars,

33
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:25,199
253 care gaps, 30 high-risk counties.

34
00:01:25,239 --> 00:01:27,000
Claude is now composing the narrative,

35
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,480
findings, anomalies, equity recommendations,

36
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:31,839
all from a single structured tool call.

37
00:01:31,839 --> 00:01:34,199
PDF export ships built in.

38
00:01:34,199 --> 00:01:36,760
This is agent composability in action.

39
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:40,400
Layer two, a Next.js dashboard on top of the same tools

40
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,360
for humans.

41
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:45,480
National view, 5426 hospitals, 3.08 average,

42
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:47,720
450 quality flags.

43
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:50,680
Filter to California and the same analysis refocuses

44
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:53,120
instantly, every facility is searchable.

45
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,480
Type UCSF, five hospitals in the system,

46
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,400
medical center rating a perfect five stars

47
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,239
across CMS quality measures.

48
00:01:59,239 --> 00:02:01,360
Compare any two facilities head-to-head.

49
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:03,800
UCSF versus Cleveland Clinic, death rates,

50
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,800
safety scores, ED wait times,

51
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:08,039
all aligned in one LLM readable view.

52
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:10,839
The equity page visualizes the disparity the tool computes.

53
00:02:10,839 --> 00:02:14,399
0.77 stars, 1,700 high-SVI facilities,

54
00:02:14,399 --> 00:02:18,440
11 tools, real data, zero PHI, built for Agents Assemble.


